div.p:
Here we are to conſider firſt the thing, a perſonall Treaty, ſecondly the place, at
London. We ſhall looke upon your reaſons with reference to both. Firſt for the thing,
your firſt reaſon is;

1.Reply. It is true, the Crowne aod Revenues goe together in England, however it is in Scotland;
neither doe we preſume any propoſitions ſhall be ſent by the Parliament, in prejudice
to the Crown or Crown-Revenues, both being for the Kingdoms honour and ſafety.
